[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Additional Issues[bold]We agree consideration should be given to better information sharing
[normal] and MASS has been in discussions with the ABI for over two years to 
[normal]find 
[normal]agreement on what data can be shared with claimant solicitors at an early
[normal] stage. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]O
[normal]ne issue on transparency 
[normal]worthy of consideration is 
[normal]around the starting of new policies. Our understanding is that when a new policy is created through a ‘broker’ (such as gocompare) the insurer has little opportunity to cancel the policy 
[normal]if there are fraudulent aspects,
[normal] before the expiry of the 14 day canc
[normal]ellation period.  We would suggest that this element needs to be investigated further in order to stop fraud at the instigation of the policy
[normal].
